----------------------------------------------------------
****** inorder to push code from local to remote repo *****
right click form your project folder and open 'git bash'
git init --> to initialize local git repo
git remote add origin https://github.com/masifpasha/nopcommerce.git -> connect local to remote repo
git config --global user.name "masifpasha" --> mostly for first time for your project
git config user.name "masifpasha@gmail.com" --> mostly for first time for your project
git status --> to see a list of all local directory, what is commited into git or not (these are untracked if they are not in staging area)
git all -A --> to add all data from your local directory to staging area
git status
git commit -m "comment for first time" --> commit to local repo
git status
git push -u origin master
now, you can see all the code in github repository.
so all the code is pushed to git remote repo

***** for getting data from remote to local repo :*******
git pull

*** again if you want to push to remote repo
git add - A
git commit -m "comment"
git push -u origin master
